{
  "texts": [
    "In this modality alignment phase, models typically leverage vast speech data to bridge the audio-text gap.",
    "A common strategy is to incorporate a pretrained speech encoder and align its acoustic representations with a text-based LLM.",
    "For example, Qwen-Audio begins with a pretrained Whisper encoder coupled to an LLM backbone via a projector [104].",
    "The alignment is refined by supervised tasks that force audio and text to correspond.",
    "Notably, automatic speech recognition (ASR) and audio captioning (AAC) are usually used as fundamental alignment tasks [27], [29].The total parameters θ of the model are composed of θ LLM, θ encoder, and θ adapter."
  ]
}